    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "A researcher wants to estimate how wide a city is based on its land area, assuming each city is shaped like a circle.\r\n\r\n✅ <strong>TO DO:</strong> In <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Research.java</code>, write the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">getCityWidth()</code> method. This method should:\r\n\r\n1. Take a city's land area as a <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">double</code> parameter.\r\n\r\n2. Use the formula <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">( √(land area ÷ π) ) × 2</code> to calculate and return the approximate width.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #E0D1EC; border: 1px solid #9660bf; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1.1em; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\r\n💡 <strong>TIP:</strong> Use <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Math.sqrt(...)</code> and <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Math.PI</code> in your calculation.\r\n</div>\r\n",
